I am not touching any core optimization code (Runner, PlacementEngine, evaluator, history store, pybind, parallel variant/exploration runners). The new multi-usecase path is a header-only CLI wrapper that sits beside the current CLI path and uses the existing Runner interface exactly as-is.

Two important behavior notes:

The new batch path is fully independent per usecase: each worker thread owns its own Runner, parsed JSON objects, output streams, and history buffers. There are no locks, no shared Runner state, no shared history state. Work dispatch is one atomic fetch_add.

The run is not tied to any GUI/screen state. On Windows, screen-off / screen-lock does not stop the process as long as the machine stays awake and does not enter sleep / hibernate.

